originalText.text: I honestly would be surprised if this woman is still working. One star is not enough to describe how awful this dentist is, trust me.  She ruined my teeth, specifically during my root canal procedure. After she was done, my tooth began to hurt and the pain continued. It was 2 years since I saw her and I still feel the pain. Now I am currently trying to find other dentists to fix the damage she caused. Oh, but I am not done yet. She legit does not know how to use her tools. You need to keep the saliva ejector in your mouth at all times but no she decided to use it whenever she felt like it. I told her that I felt pain, but then she ignored me and said she saw nothing like what I said meant nothing to her. Then after I had to spit, she told me not to spit or else I would get the area infected. That completely did not make sense, where else would I spit on the floor? Lastly, I contacted her on the phone and I swear this woman needs to get her life together because for some reason there was always an attitude and she screamed at me for no reason. I was being respectful, but I guess that meant nothing to her. If you had common sense you would not visit this dentist.

originalText.text: This dentist is the worst I've ever had. When I went in to get something fixed in my tooth she pulls out this BIG thick needle to insert into my gum in order to numb it and proceed with the procedure, which can obviously cause fear in anyone. When she notices I'm scared of the needle and hesitate a bit she literally tells me this "please stop and get it together because you are not a baby and it's already 5pm and I have to go home and leave so let's hurry this up or else you can just go" but in Spanish. What kind of doctor speaks to their patient like that?  She is the most unprofessional and unsympathetic doctor ever. Once I cooperated and let her insert the needle she says this comment to me: "oh my goodness look at how dramatic you were being. I hope you have enough tears left for when your boyfriend leaves you because you just cried them all out today". Purely awful human being this woman is. If you want to be treated and spoken to like an animal then by all means go to her. I was always kind to her however she seemed to have her own personal issue with me that I never caused or even provoked. I reported her to HealthFirst because she needs to learn how to keep her mouth shut, be kind and patient, and do her job, rather than invade other peoples' personal affairs and speak to them as if they're her friends.
